In [17]:
def mfcc_features_extract(x):

    features_mfcc = []
    try:
        x , sr = librosa.load(x)
        features_mfcc = librosa.feature.mfcc(y=x, sr=sr, n_mfcc=128)
        features_mfcc = np.mean(features_mfcc.T,axis=0)
    except:
        print('Error reading audio')
    return features_mfcc

MODEL BUILDING¶

In [136]:
tf.keras.backend.clear_session()
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.InputLayer(input_shape=(16, 8, 1)),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding = "same"),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=8, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding = "same"),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),
    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(len(d['Index in Corpus'].unique()), activation='softmax')
])

Comments and Conclusion:¶

As the accuracy was only 46%, we can see words are not correctly classified, out of 4,¶

1 was classified as "Darmyana": Raat¶

1 was classified as "Kaam" : Saal¶

1 was classified as "Tamaam" : Aaj¶

1 was classified as "Darmyana" : Kal¶

Scaling and feeding the mfcc train and val datasets, gives 46% accuracy.¶

Tried different modeling approaches as:¶

PCA, degraded accuracy and gave 20% accuracy with CNN¶

PCA and SVM(linear) degraded accuracy and gave app 6% accuracy¶

PCA and SVM(rbf) degraded accuracy and gave 0% accuracy¶

PCA and Decision Tree Classifier also degraded and gave 6.7% accuracy¶

PCA and RandomForest Classifier improved but still degraded and gave 6.7% accuracy¶

Scaled + PCA approach gave 0% or similar/same as above accuracy for all above models.¶

Directly sending scaled X_train and X_val without PCA approach to Decision Tree gave 20% accuracy¶

Random Fiorest gave 13.3% accuracy for above¶

SVM(rbf) and SVM(linear) gave 0% accuracy for the same.¶

Hence best accuracy was given by our CNN, giving 46% accuracy, which still is not that great.¶

We might get better accuracy if we increase the size of our dataset.¶
